This paper discusses the design and implementation of a machine learning-based algorithm used in Wikipedia, which involves computer science (cs) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the values and preferences of the Wikipedia community, which relates to social and information retrieval (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation and improvement of the algorithm, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR).
